# ScrambleCoin StarterBot — environment variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values.
# Then load it before running: `export $(cat .env | xargs) && dotnet run`

# Base URL of the ScrambleCoin API server (no trailing slash)
BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Display name for this bot (used in console output only)
BOT_NAME=MyBot

# (Optional) Bot identity token — a stable UUID that identifies this bot to the server.
# The server requires X-Bot-Token on queue and join endpoints to prevent duplicate queuing.
# If not set, a new random UUID is generated at startup (meaning each run appears as a new bot).
# For persistent identity across restarts, generate once and keep here:
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomUUID())"  OR  uuidgen
# BOT_TOKEN=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx

# (Optional) Join a specific pre-created game instead of using matchmaking.
# Leave blank or unset to use the matchmaking queue.
# GAME_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
